 ** story time ** 
 my airpods pro did not come with all of the materials that come in the original box and the charger i received [packaged separately] was not even an apple brand. this did not bother me a lot, so i have more than covech accessories for this item. 
 the device itself appeared clean and undamaged. when i opned the device to check the battery status, it was dead [apple has a policy of not sending their devices fully charged for shipping safety reasons, so i assumed the previous owner received the item new and returned them without charging it more]. 
 i connected the airpods to my office apple charger from a prior device and the battery light immedialy glowed green. confused, i the proceeded to pair it to my phone. the first attempt was successful. i checked my battery notification screen on my iphone and the airpods case displayed a full 100% charge, yet the airpods themselves were each dead at 1%. after few seconds of charge, they rear 7% [charging speed rare, but not completely unheard of], so i took the case off the charger and went to test out the sound quality. 
 as so i took an earpiece out- the entire device went off. the case and pods still read as charging on my phone even though i had removed them from charging moments before. i could not find the devise in my drop menu, so i went into settitins to manually pair the airpods again-sy wooldn’t sync. after 4/5 times connecting and forgetting device, i attempted to reattach the charger- now the airpods case is on 0% but the earpieces arery on 13% 🙄. as soon i plug them back in, the airpods sync again and i able to hear the pairing chime on my earpiece. seconds later the airpods die and the phone shows they are on 0% * charging * while they are still in my ears! 
 like i said, i have had a ton of airpods, i know how to troubleot most any problem they give me. i have never had to deal with this kind of headache before- specially on day 1. i am so over it! i am going to an apple store first thing in the morning. this was a horrible experience.

do not purchase ‘renewed’ airpods. i listen to podcasts and audiobooks. as such, i have purchaseed many earbuds over the last 10 years, most of which were <$ 100. wanting a durable earbud with good audio (particularly for making / receiving calls), i finally chose the apple pro. to save money i chose a ‘renewed’ apple product. 
 i made my purchase on nov 19, and have been vray content with the quality - so so so that i decided to order another pair for my wife on dec 8. however, on dec 9 i began having connection problems with my earbuds. so i decided to do what i summes do with amazon, and decide to exchange. this is when i discovered the pitfalls of buying a ‘renewed’ apple product. 
 first, unlike most amazon purchases, there is no return / exchange option for renewed apple earpods. there is, however, bureaucracy. after closer look at my options and an hour on the phone with amazon and apple, i discovered that my earbud warranty (with the sell) expired on dec 10. my only option was to send the buds to apple for repair. 
 i immedialy decided to cancel my second amazon (earbud) order. however, just like my first order, there was no cancel option for the second earbuds. they were in the mail. i received them the next day. 
 at this time i have initiedated returns through customer service and i am waiting for follow up via amazon. i will modify this review accordingly. 
 the lesson, if you want apple earpods, buy new.
